<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1399,1108,1246]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
This species was described based on two male specimens collected by Francisco Campos Ribadeneira in Posorja (“Posoya”), 
<collectingCountry box="[461,561,1145,1171]" name="Ecuador" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
. Campos (
<date box="[685,820,1145,1171]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1878" valueMax="1943">1878–1943</date>
) was an intellectual from Guayaquil and the first Ecuadorian entomologist (
<bibRefCitation author="Barragan" box="[504,760,1182,1208]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Barragan" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="410 - 423" refId="ref19183" refString="Barragan A. R., Dangles O., Cardenas R. E. &amp; Onore G. 2009. The history of entomology in Ecuador. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France (n. s.) 45: 410 - 423. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00379271.2009.10697626" type="journal article" year="2009">
Barragán 
<emphasis box="[624,686,1182,1208]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
). He collected numerous insects and created the first entomological collection in that country (
<bibRefCitation author="Moret" box="[673,818,1219,1246]" firstAuthor="Moret" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref21267" refString="Moret P. 2005. Los coleopteros Carabidae del paramo en los Andes del Ecuador. Sistematica, ecologia y biogeografia. Museo de Zoologia, Centro de Biodiversidad y Ambiente, Escuela de Biologia. Pontificia Universidad Catolica del Ecuador, Quito." type="book" year="2005">Moret 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1399,1286,1423]" lastBlockId="8.[189,1399,267,332]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
